      <section eId="sec_44_14_182">
        <num>44-14-182</num>
        <content>
          <p>An endorsement to order or in blank by the payee of a mortgage note gives the endorsee or the holder for value the right to foreclose the mortgage in his own name. A mortgage transferred without written assignment may be foreclosed in the name of the mortgagee bringing the action for the use of such assignee; and proceedings begun in the name of the transferee may be amended by making the mortgagee a party before or after the judgment.</p>
          <p>(Civil Code 1895, ยง 2745; Civil Code 1910, ยง 3278; Code 1933, ยง 67-203.)</p>
